com.SCHSRobotics.HAL9001.system.robot

Annotation Type InternalCamera


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=FIELD)
public @interface InternalCamera
    An annotation meant to be used on OpenCVCamera objects or their subclasses in order to specify that they are external cameras and to provide information about how to create them.

    Creation Date: 9/24/20

    Since:
    1.1.0
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Cole Savage, Level Up
    See Also:
    ExternalCamera, CameraManager, Robot

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      int resHeight
      The camera resolution height in pixels.
      int resWidth
      The camera resolution width in pixels.
      boolean usesViewport
      Whether or not the camera uses the viewport to display output video.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      org.openftc.easyopencv.OpenCvInternalCamera.CameraDirection direction
      The internal camera direction (FRONT or BACK).
